<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: zyerne</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-17 14:05:35</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Just my cp idea for easy increase of factions:<BR>
<BR>
If you want to up your factions with the Corrupt Qeynos <BR>
guards and are willing to go to Erudin(and allowed there, <BR>
there is an EASY quest that you can keep running to do <BR>
to up the faction.<BR>
<BR>
3rd floor in the "castle" - where the bank is, there is a <BR>
guy named Toresian Fhabe. He is waiting for someone to take <BR>
inert potion to the Vials of Vitality (which is on the 1st <BR>
floor of the same building)<BR>
<BR>
Go down to Vials and give the potion to Slansin. He is a <BR>
gate bandit and will laugh and tell you that he is not <BR>
the right Slansin. In return,  the following factions<BR>
go up:  Coalition of Trade Folk Ill, Coalition of Tradefolk,<BR>
 Carson McCabe, Corrupt Qeynos Guards and The Freeport <BR>
Militia. <BR>
<BR>
If you can tolerate running the stairs for a while, it is a <BR>
very simple way to up those factions without lowering any <BR>
others, as well as not wasting mana or getting attacked.<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
So, is the person who said you can do this quest without <BR>
going to HP ever going to share with the rest of us <BR>
non-happy campers? :)<BR>
<BR>
Zyerne<BR>
Erudite Cleric</font></td></tr></table>
